            'data' => '{"faqs": [{"answer": "If you want to study in Canada, you should aim for a GPA of 2.8 or higher.", "question": "How much GPA is required to study in Canada from Nepal?"}, {"answer": "The cost of studying in Canada will vary depending on the institution you choose and the program you enroll in. On average, international students can expect to pay between $15,000 and $30,000 per year for tuition.", "question": "What is the cost of studying in Canada?"}, {"answer": "Yes, as a study permit holder, you are allowed to work part-time on campus and full-time during scheduled breaks. However, you will need to obtain a work permit in order to work off campus.", "question": "Can I work while studying in Canada?"}, {"answer": "Yes, after you graduate from a designated learning institution in Canada, you may be eligible to apply for a post-graduation work permit, which allows you to work in Canada for a period of time that is related to the length of your study program. This can help you gain Canadian work experience and potentially qualify for permanent residence in Canada.", "question": "Can I stay in Canada after I graduate?"}, {"answer": "After completing your studies in Canada, you may be eligible to apply for a work permit, which will allow you to work in Canada for a specific period of time.", "question": "Is it easy to find a job in Canada after studying?"}, {"answer": "There are many scholarships available for international students who are studying in Canada. Scholarships can be offered by the Canadian government, educational institutions, or private organizations. The availability and eligibility requirements for scholarships will vary, so it is important to research the different scholarships available and determine which ones you may be eligible for.", "question": "Are scholarships available for international students in Canada?"}, {"answer": "The requirements and process for applying for permanent residency will vary depending on your individual circumstances, such as the province you are in, your level of education, and your work experience. It is important to research the requirements and process for applying for permanent residency before you arrive in Canada.", "question": "Can I apply for permanent residency after studying in Canada?"}, {"answer": "In general, the weather in Canada is cold in the winter and mild in the summer. However, the weather can vary greatly depending on the region you are in. For example, the west coast of Canada has a milder climate, while the east coast has a more extreme climate with colder winters and warmer summers.", "question": "What is the weather like in Canada?"}, {"answer": "The Canadian way of life is enriching and rewarding for international students from all over the world. Canadian universities and colleges are filled with world-class facilities, sports, extracurricular activities, and cultural programs.", "question": "Is student life easy in Canada?"}], "description": "<h2>Why Study in Canada from Nepal?</h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>When anybody mentions Canada, what comes to mind? Is it the merciless winters, the hockey-loving Canadians, or the maple syrup it is renowned for?</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Well, you might have heard that Canadians ride polar bears to work and apologize all the time, but Canada is also one of the best countries in the world when it comes to education. It is one of the top choice for Nepalese students looking to study abroad. It offers&nbsp;<strong>reputed and affordable education</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>immigration options</strong>, and&nbsp;<strong>employment opportunities</strong>.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Known for its natural beauty, diverse culture, welcoming people, and high standard of living, Canada is a popular destination for international students. If you&rsquo;re a student from Nepal considering studying in Canada, keep reading to learn everything you need to know.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Facts about Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Canada is a world leader in language training. 21% of all Canadian people speak a foreign language as a native language. 40% of these people speak European and 56% speak Asian.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Canada has more lakes than any other country in the world.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>51% of the international students studying in Canada intend to apply for&nbsp;<strong>permanent residence</strong>.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Basketball was invented in Canada.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Canada is rich in natural resources.</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>There were 1,090,000 full-time and 266,000 part-time students in 2019 in Canadian universities.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li><strong>1,794500 new jobs</strong>&nbsp;were created for graduates between 2009 and 2019.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>78% of universities in Canada promote intercultural engagement through different events and activities.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The&nbsp;<strong>cost of living is lower</strong>&nbsp;when compared to other top student destinations.</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Canada has very high standards of living and some of the most livable cities in the world are in Canada.</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Reasons to Study in Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Canada attracts thousands of international students each year from countries all over the world. In recent years, Canada has seen a significant increase in the number of international students. Here are 5 reasons why you should choose Canada for higher education:</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>1. Reputed Education System</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Canada is globally recognized for its high-quality education system. Canadian universities and colleges consistently rank among the top institutions in the world. The country is known for its academic excellence, high standards, and innovative research opportunities. A degree from a Canadian institution is highly valued and respected worldwide.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>2. Post-Study Work Opportunities</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Canada offers excellent post-study work opportunities for international students. After completing their studies, graduates can apply for a Post-Graduation Work Permit (PGWP) that allows them to work in Canada for up to&nbsp;<strong>3 years</strong>. This work experience can be valuable for career development and can potentially lead to permanent residency options.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>3. Affordable Tuition Fees</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Compared to other popular study destinations, Canada offers relatively affordable tuition fees for international students. The&nbsp;<a href=\\"https://thenext.edu.np/total-cost-to-study-in-canada-from-nepal/\\">total cost</a>&nbsp;of education in Canada is generally lower than in countries like the United States, the United Kingdom, or Australia. Also, there are numerous&nbsp;<strong>scholarships</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;grants</strong>, and funding options available to help support international students financially.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>4. Natural Beauty &amp; Quality of Life</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Canada is renowned for its breathtaking landscapes, including stunning mountains, lakes, and vast forests. It offers numerous outdoor activities, such as hiking, skiing, and wildlife exploration, allowing students to experience a unique blend of natural beauty and adventure. Also, Canadian cities consistently rank among the best for quality of life, a high standard of living, safety, and excellent healthcare facilities.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>5. Multicultural Society and Safe Environment</h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Canada is known for its diverse and inclusive society. It welcomes people from all backgrounds and cultures, providing a multicultural environment that fosters&nbsp;<strong>cross-cultural learning</strong>&nbsp;and understanding. Canadians are generally friendly and open-minded, making it easier for international students to adapt and feel at home. Moreover, Canada is considered one of the safest countries in the world, ensuring a secure and peaceful learning environment.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Student Visa Process for Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The student visa process for Canada requires a few essential steps. Firstly, you need to secure acceptance from a designated learning institution (DLI) in Canada. Next, you should review the specific visa requirements for your country of residence and gather the necessary documents. Then, you can submit your study permit application online through the IRCC website, providing accurate information and proof of financial support. If required, undergo a medical examination and provide biometric information. Finally, wait for the application to be processed and receive a decision.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Cost to Study in Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Below is the comprehensive table outlining the average annual tuition fees for international students in Canada, categorized by the level of study:</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<table>\\r\\n\\t<thead>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<th>Level of Study</th>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<th>Average Annual Tuition Fees (in CAD)</th>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t</thead>\\r\\n\\t<tbody>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>Undergraduate Courses</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>$12,000 &ndash; $25,000</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>Postgraduate Courses</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>$18,000 &ndash; $30,000</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>PhD Courses</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>$7,000 &ndash; $18,000</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>Masters of Business Administration Courses</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td>$32,000 &ndash; $45,000</td>\\r\\n\\t\\t</tr>\\r\\n\\t</tbody>\\r\\n</table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Note: These figures are average estimates and can vary significantly depending on the university,&nbsp;<a href=\\"https://thenext.edu.np/popular-courses-to-study-in-canada/\\">p</a>rogram, and specific circumstances. It&rsquo;s always advisable to consult the official websites of the institutions you are interested in to get the most up-to-date information about tuition fees for your chosen field of study.</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Popular Courses in Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Engineering</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Computer Science &amp;&nbsp;<a href=\\"https://thenext.edu.np/5-popular-it-courses-in-canada/\\">I</a>T</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Business</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Law</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Hospitality and Tourism Hotel Management</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Media and Communication</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Education</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Architecture</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Economics</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Fine Arts</li>\\r\\n</ol>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>Best Cities to Study in Canada</strong></h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li>Toronto</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Montreal</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Vancouver</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ottawa</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Quebec</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Edmonton</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Calgary</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Winnipeg</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Waterloo</li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Halifax</li>\\r\\n</ol>"}',
